---
import LegalLayout from "../layouts/LegalLayout.astro";

const sections = [
  { id: "what-it-is", title: "What Kârly is" },
  { id: "not-advice", title: "Not financial advice" },
  { id: "account", title: "No account needed" },
  { id: "free-tier", title: "Free tier & limits" },
  { id: "pro-tier", title: "Pro tier & billing" },
  { id: "refunds", title: "Refunds & cancellation" },
  { id: "acceptable-use", title: "Acceptable use" },
  { id: "availability", title: "Availability" },
  { id: "warranty", title: "No warranty" },
  { id: "liability", title: "Limit of liability" },
  { id: "changes", title: "Changes to these terms" },
  { id: "contact", title: "Contact" },
];
---

<LegalLayout
  eyebrow="Terms of service"
  title="The deal between us."
  lede="By using Kârly, you agree to these terms. We've tried to keep them short, fair, and in plain English. No fine-print booby traps."
  description="Kârly's terms of service. The deal between you and us, in plain English."
  lastUpdated="May 13, 2026"
  meta={["v0.2", "Governing law · Türkiye"]}
  sections={sections}
>
  <section id="what-it-is">
    <h2>What Kârly is</h2>
    <p>
      Kârly is a mobile calculator that runs the same profit math across ten
      marketplaces. You type your numbers, we apply each marketplace&rsquo;s
      default commission, VAT and listing fees, and show you a net profit,
      margin, ROI, and breakeven price.
    </p>
    <p>
      &ldquo;Kârly,&rdquo; &ldquo;the app,&rdquo; and &ldquo;we&rdquo; mean
      the Kârly software, made by NexUtility. &ldquo;You&rdquo; means whoever
      is using the app — usually a small online seller.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="not-advice">
    <h2>Not financial, tax, or legal advice</h2>
    <div class="callout">
      Kârly is a calculator, not an accountant. The numbers we show are the
      result of arithmetic on the inputs you provide, against the public
      default rates each marketplace publishes. Real-world commissions can
      vary by category, seller tier, region, and negotiation. Real-world
      taxes depend on your jurisdiction and your particular setup.
    </div>
    <p>
      Use Kârly to estimate, not to file taxes. For anything that matters
      legally or financially, talk to an accountant or tax advisor licensed
      in your jurisdiction.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="account">
    <h2>No account needed</h2>
    <p>
      There is no sign-up. There is no login. There is no Kârly password to
      forget. The app works as soon as you install it. Your data is stored
      on your device — see our
      <a class="inline" href="/privacy">privacy policy</a> for specifics.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="free-tier">
    <h2>Free tier &amp; limits</h2>
    <p>The free tier of Kârly includes:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Access to all ten marketplaces and the full calculator</li>
      <li>
        Up to three calculations per local-time day (counter resets at
        midnight your time)
      </li>
      <li>Unlimited PDF reports of the calculations you do run</li>
      <li>Light and dark themes, English and Türkçe interface</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      The free tier does not include History (saving past calculations) or
      the cross-marketplace Compare view.
    </p>
    <p>
      We may change the daily limit in future versions if we need to. If we
      do, we&rsquo;ll explain why in a release note. We won&rsquo;t drop it
      below something reasonable.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="pro-tier">
    <h2>Pro tier &amp; billing</h2>
    <p>
      Kârly Pro is a paid subscription that removes the daily calculation
      cap and unlocks History plus the Compare view. Pricing is shown in the
      app and may differ slightly between regions because app stores convert
      currencies.
    </p>
    <p>
      Billing is handled by your platform&rsquo;s app store — Google Play
      Billing on Android. We do not handle your payment information
      directly. We use RevenueCat as a thin layer to validate your
      subscription status on your device.
    </p>
    <p>
      Pro subscriptions auto-renew at the end of each billing period unless
      you cancel them in your app store account before the renewal date. We
      don&rsquo;t, and can&rsquo;t, charge you outside of your app store.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="refunds">
    <h2>Refunds &amp; cancellation</h2>
    <p>
      You can cancel a Pro subscription at any time in your Google Play
      account. Cancellation takes effect at the end of the current billing
      period — you keep Pro access until then, and we do not pro-rate
      refunds.
    </p>
    <p>
      If something went genuinely wrong (you were charged twice, a feature
      you paid for is broken, you bought Pro by accident on a kid&rsquo;s
      account), write to
      <a class="inline" href="mailto:hi@nexutility.com">hi@nexutility.com</a>
      and we&rsquo;ll work it out. Refund issuance for app store purchases
      ultimately runs through Google or Apple&rsquo;s refund flow, which
      we&rsquo;ll help you navigate.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="acceptable-use">
    <h2>Acceptable use</h2>
    <p>Don&rsquo;t do any of these things with Kârly:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Decompile, reverse-engineer, or modify the app&rsquo;s binaries</li>
      <li>
        Scrape, automate, or otherwise abuse the app in a way that bypasses
        the Pro subscription
      </li>
      <li>
        Use the app to commit fraud (e.g. mock up fake PDF profit reports to
        deceive a third party)
      </li>
      <li>Resell, sublicense, or redistribute the app or its assets</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      If you do, we may stop providing service to you. Given there is no
      account, this is mostly theoretical — but it&rsquo;s worth saying.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="availability">
    <h2>Availability</h2>
    <p>
      Kârly is currently published for Android in Türkiye and globally
      where Google Play allows. iOS is on the roadmap but not committed to a
      date. The app does not require an internet connection for the
      calculator itself, but app store features (purchasing Pro, restoring
      purchases, app updates) do.
    </p>
    <p>
      If you live in a country where we cannot legally provide the app, or
      where your app store does not list it, we are not able to make it
      available to you. We do not provide sideloaded builds.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="warranty">
    <h2>No warranty</h2>
    <p>
      Kârly is provided <em>as is</em>. We try hard to make the math
      correct, the marketplace defaults current, and the app reliable — but
      we make no formal warranty that it will be uninterrupted, bug-free, or
      that it will produce the exact same number a marketplace&rsquo;s own
      dashboard produces (those dashboards have access to your specific
      seller tier; Kârly uses public defaults, which you can override).
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="liability">
    <h2>Limit of liability</h2>
    <p>
      To the maximum extent permitted by applicable law, NexUtility&rsquo;s
      total liability arising out of or relating to Kârly is limited to the
      amount you paid us for Kârly Pro in the twelve months before the
      claim arose (or, for free-tier users, zero — because that&rsquo;s what
      you paid us).
    </p>
    <p>
      We are not liable for indirect, incidental, or consequential damages —
      for example, lost profits from a listing decision you made using a
      Kârly estimate. The calculator is a tool; the decision is yours.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="changes">
    <h2>Changes to these terms</h2>
    <p>
      We may update these terms when we ship a new version with materially
      different mechanics — for example, adding a new paid tier, or
      changing the free-tier cap. When we do, we&rsquo;ll update the
      &ldquo;Last updated&rdquo; date at the top and surface a notice on
      the next app launch. If a change is unfavorable to you, you can
      simply stop using the app, and any active Pro subscription can be
      cancelled in your app store.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="contact">
    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions about these terms, or about a specific billing or account
      issue? Write to
      <a class="inline" href="mailto:hi@nexutility.com">hi@nexutility.com</a>.
    </p>
    <p style="margin-top:24px; font-size: 14px; color: var(--subtle)">
      Kârly is a product of NexUtility, established in Türkiye. Governing
      law for these terms is Turkish law, and any dispute will be resolved
      in the courts of Istanbul — unless local consumer-protection rules in
      your country give you a different mandatory forum, in which case
      those rules win.
    </p>
  </section>
</LegalLayout>
